          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Demand for land rights</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/indigenous-land-rights-protest-brazil-global-activists.png" alt="Indigenous activists from around the world rallied in Brazil, demanding stronger protections for ancestral lands and human rights" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Indigenous activists from around the world rallied in Brazil, demanding stronger protections for ancestral lands and human rights. Credits: Green Peace</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">In the ‚Äúlargest mobilization of Indigenous people,‚Äù 8,000 participants from over 135 ethnic groups demanded the demarcation of Indigenous lands and the protection of natural resources at the annual <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-04-2025-h2-3-acampamento-terra-livre" target="_blank">Acampamento Terra Livre</a> event. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Representatives from the Amazon Basin nations and Oceania signed a joint manifesto emphasizing the role of Indigenous peoples in preserving the ecosystem. Sergio Marworno, a prominent Indigenous leader from the state of Amap√°, asserted that the Territorial and Environmental Management Plans (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-04-2025-h2-4-pgtas" target="_blank">PGTAs</a>) provide guidelines for fighting climate change from within their communities.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Norway‚Äôs ambassador to Brazil signed a cooperation agreement with the Xingu Indigenous Land Association to support a sustainable development initiative. Meanwhile, France donated ‚Ç¨1M ($1.12M) to three Indigenous organizations after the US pulled the plug on USAID. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Jair Bolsonaro‚Äôs administration halted land demarcation. However, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-04-2025-h2-5-the-decree" target="_blank">the decree</a> passed in January reinforced the power of the National Indian Foundation (Funai), which protects the demarcated lands from land grabbers.</p>
        </mj-text>
